  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb3 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u2013 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka resumes talks with IMF - Finance Ministry",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka has started negotiations with the International Monetary Fund to recover from the economic crisis after the new government took office, the Ministry of Finance said.",
        "Negotiations with the International Monetary Fund began in April under the Gotabaya Rajapaksa government.",
        "The Sri Lankan government is seeking much-needed EV aid to tackle the country's worst economic crisis since 1948 - a condition the government will have to carry out economic reforms.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe was appointed President after President Rajapaksa was ousted by a popular uprising caused by a months-long shortage of medicines, food and fuel.",
        "Wickremesinghe, who served as Prime Minister six times, intends to engage in debt restructuring.",
        "Negotiations with the International Monetary Fund appear to have been largely successful and Sri Lanka is working with consultants to reach a compromise agreement with creditors, the government said."
      ],
